        <link rel="schema.DC" href="https://purl.org/DC/elements/1.0/" /><meta name="citation_journal_title" content="RadioGraphics" /><meta name="dc.Title" content="Male Breast Disease: Pictorial Review with Radiologic-Pathologic Correlation" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Cheri  Nguyen" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Mark D.  Kettler" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Michael E.  Swirsky" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Vivian I.  Miller" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Caleb  Scott" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Rhett  Krause" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Jennifer A.  Hadro" /><meta name="dc.Description" content="The embryology and anatomy of the male breast are reviewed and a spectrum of benign and malignant processes affecting the male breast are discussed, with emphasis on mammographic and US findings an..." /><meta name="Description" content="The embryology and anatomy of the male breast are reviewed and a spectrum of benign and malignant processes affecting the male breast are discussed, with emphasis on mammographic and US findings an..." /><meta name="dc.Description" content="The male breast is susceptible to many of the same pathologic processes as the female breast. Many of these conditions have mammographic, ultrasonographic (US), and magnetic resonance imaging findi..." /><meta name="Description" content="The male breast is susceptible to many of the same pathologic processes as the female breast. Many of these conditions have mammographic, ultrasonographic (US), and magnetic resonance imaging findi..." /><meta name="dc.Publisher" content="Radiological Society of North America" /><meta name="dc.Date" scheme="WTN8601" content="2013-05-03" /><meta name="dc.Type" content="research-article" /><meta name="dc.Format" content="text/HTML" /><meta name="dc.Identifier" scheme="publisher-id" content="125137" /><meta name="dc.Identifier" scheme="doi" content="10.1148/rg.333125137" /><meta name="dc.Source" content="https://doi.org/10.1148/